</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED5E383AFF78F98FFBE5F7D7" pageId="527" pageNumber="528" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFF78F98FFC73FE8E" blockId="527.[136,778,1329,2071]" lastBlockId="527.[810,1452,173,1696]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED5E383AFF78F98FFE77F99A" bold="true" box="[189,434,1601,1627]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Description of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFDC3F98FFDB0F99D" box="[518,629,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351A</figureCitation>
) of ovigerous adult extremely swollen. Smaller young adult (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFD54F9ADFCC7F9BF" box="[657,770,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351B</figureCitation>
) stout, but not as swollen. Body surface densely ornamented with minute setules. Prosome of ovigerous adult 1.57 mm long; dorsal cephalic shield bearing acutely pointed, paired horn-like processes posterolaterally (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFD41F922FD3BF8C7" box="[644,766,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351C</figureCitation>
). Metasome with 2 or 3 dorsal constrictions, marking original articulations between somites; fourth pedigeroussomite (or fusedthirdand fourthpedigerous somites) greatly expanded, almost spherical, forming brood pouch. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFD1BF8BAFF00F870" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351D</figureCitation>
) small, inserted into ventral surface of prosome, 5- segmented, but posterior articulations indistinct. Genital somite 49×193 μm; abdominal somites covered with minutesetules, 36×167, 58×149, 33×138, and 73×135 μm, respectively. Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFBA2FF63FB1DFF09" box="[1127,1240,173,200]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351E</figureCitation>
) stronglytapering, about 1.8 times longer than wide (71×40 μm) and as long as anal somite, densely covered with setules; narrowed distal part pale and with thin cuticle: caudal setae not discernible from setules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFC9AFE96FA9BFD40" blockId="527.[810,1452,173,1696]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFC09FE99FBFDFEB3" box="[972,1080,343,370]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351F</figureCitation>
) aslongas wide, denselysetulose, weak, flexible, with rounded distal margin. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFCF7FE55FC60FE77" box="[818,933,411,438]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351G</figureCitation>
) stronglytapering, incompletely 7-segmented, 160 μm long; setae not discernible from setules. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFCF7FE11FC6DFE3B" box="[818,936,479,506]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351H</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented, consistingof coxa, basis, and unsegmented endopod; endopodal segment 2.9 times longer than wide (55×19 μm) and 0.7 times as long as basis: armedwith 6 setae (grouped as 1, 2, and 3) plus small terminal claw, one-third as long as endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFC9AFD47FC48FAC6" blockId="527.[810,1452,173,1696]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFC0AFD47FB85FD65" box="[975,1088,649,676]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351I</figureCitation>
) with broad convex posterior margin; posterior region soft, flexible, densely setulose. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFC67FD03FBCFFD29" box="[930,1034,717,744]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351J</figureCitation>
) with 5 acute teeth and 1 small setaon coxalgnathobase: basiswith 1 medial seta: exopodwith 5 setae, outersetaeslightlyshorterthan others:endopodwith 1 and 4 setae on first and second segments, respectively; proportional lengths of setae on second segment 3:4:6:5 from inner to outer. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFB46FCB9FB33FC53" box="[1155,1270,887,914]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351K</figureCitation>
) with 7 setae on arthrite, 1 each on epipodite and basis, 4 on exopod and 3 on endopod; coxal endite absent; 3 setae on endopod unequal (medial seta shortest and outer seta longest). Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFC55FC31FBC1FBDB" box="[912,1028,1023,1050]" captionStart="FIGURE 352" captionStartId="529.[136,245,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[165,1446,219,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-18@529.[136,1451,195,1451]" captionTargetPageId="529" captionText="FIGURE 352. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4. Scale bars: A, C–E, 0.05 mm; B, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592018/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 352A</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; syncoxawith 4, 2, and 2 setaeon first to third endites, respectively; basis with thick seta plus 1 small seta; endopod 2-segmented with thick seta on first segment and 1 thick and 2 shorter, thin setaeon second. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFBB0FB49FB2CFB63" box="[1141,1257,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURE 352" captionStartId="529.[136,245,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[165,1446,219,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-18@529.[136,1451,195,1451]" captionTargetPageId="529" captionText="FIGURE 352. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4. Scale bars: A, C–E, 0.05 mm; B, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592018/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 352B</figureCitation>
) as unsegmented lobe bearing 5 or 6 (commonly 6) setae mediodistally and ornamented with fine spinules on distal and outer surfaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFC9AFADEFB3DF961" blockId="527.[810,1452,173,1696]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
Leg 1 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFC7FFAC1FBF5FAEB" box="[954,1072,1295,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 352" captionStartId="529.[136,245,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[165,1446,219,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-18@529.[136,1451,195,1451]" captionTargetPageId="529" captionText="FIGURE 352. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4. Scale bars: A, C–E, 0.05 mm; B, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592018/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 352C</figureCitation>
) with incompletely 3-segmented rami; inner distal spine on basis 15 μm long, bilaterally serrate; both rami ornamented with slender setules; second exopodal segment lacking outer element. Inner coxal seta absentin legs 1–4. Legs 2–4 with 3-segmented exopods and 2-segmented endopods (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFBFDFA77FB0BFA15" box="[1080,1230,1465,1492]" captionStart="FIGURE 352" captionStartId="529.[136,245,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[165,1446,219,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-18@529.[136,1451,195,1451]" captionTargetPageId="529" captionText="FIGURE 352. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4. Scale bars: A, C–E, 0.05 mm; B, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592018/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 352D, E</figureCitation>
); secondendopodal segment of legs 2 and 3 with vestige of articulation: first exopodal segment lacking inner seta. Second exopodal segment bearing minute inner seta in legs 2 and 3, but lacking in leg 4. Legs 2 and 3 with same armature formula. Proximal 2 inner setae on endopod of legs 2 and 3 minute. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFC6EF904FAB7F88B" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
<table id="F96DC47DED5EC5CAFCEFF904FA62F88B" box="[810,1447,1738,1866]" gridcols="4" gridrows="2" inLine="true" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
<tr id="355D349FED5EC5CAFCEFF904FA62F925" box="[810,1447,1738,1764]" gridrow="0" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
<th id="768C5DE3ED5EC5CAFCEFF904FB27F925" box="[810,1250,1738,1764]" colspan="3" colspanRight="2" gridcol="0" gridrow="0" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Coxa Basis Exopod</th>
<td id="768C5DE3ED5EC5CAFB3FF904FA62F925" box="[1274,1447,1738,1764]" gridcol="3" gridrow="0" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Endopod</td>
</tr>
<tr id="355D349FED5EC5CAFCEFF922FA62F88B" box="[810,1447,1772,1866]" gridrow="1" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
<th id="768C5DE3ED5EC5CAFCEFF922FC15F88B" box="[810,976,1772,1866]" gridcol="0" gridrow="1" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Leg 1 0-0 Legs 2 &amp; 30-0 Leg 4 0-0</th>
<td id="768C5DE3ED5EC5CAFC35F922FBD0F88B" box="[1008,1045,1772,1866]" gridcol="1" gridrow="1" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">1-I 1-0 1-0</td>
<td id="768C5DE3ED5EC5CAFBF2F922FB27F88B" box="[1079,1250,1772,1866]" gridcol="2" gridrow="1" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">1-1; 0-1; 2, 1, 3 1-0; 1-1; 3, 1, 5 1-0; 1-0; 2, 1, 5</td>
<td id="768C5DE3ED5EC5CAFB3FF922FA62F88B" box="[1274,1447,1772,1866]" gridcol="3" gridrow="1" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">0-1; 0-1; 1, 2, 2 0-1; 1, 2, 4 0-0; 1, 2, 2</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFC9AF8BAFB84F835" blockId="527.[810,1452,1908,2070]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED5E383AFC7AF8BAFBFCF84E" box="[959,1081,1908,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 351" captionStartId="528.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,214,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-19@528.[210,1377,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="528" captionText="FIGURE 351. Loboixys sibogae sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus of young adult, right; C, cephalic horn; D. leg 5 and urosome, ventral; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, labrum; J, mandible; K, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C, E–K, 0.02 mm; D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592016/files/figure.png" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Fig. 351D</figureCitation>
) represented by 2 small lobes positioned posteroventrally on somite; outer lobe tipped withsmall protopodal seta, and inner (exopodal) lobe tipped with 2 small setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED5E383AFC9AF832FBE5F7D7" blockId="527.[810,1452,1908,2070]" box="[863,1056,2044,2070]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED5E383AFC9AF832FC59F7D7" bold="true" box="[863,924,2044,2070]" pageId="527" pageNumber="528">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
