<subSubSection id="C3776556ED403824FF78F9AAFE86F7D7" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED403824FF78F9AAFE4BF84F" blockId="529.[136,778,1635,2070]" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FF78F9AAFEEFF9BF" bold="true" box="[189,298,1636,1662]" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FEFBF9ADFDC3F9BC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[318,518,1635,1661]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibogae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FEFBF9ADFDC3F9BC" box="[318,518,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">Loboixys sibogae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FDD6F9AAFDB7F9BF" bold="true" box="[531,626,1636,1662]" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED403824FDD6F9AAFDB7F9BF" box="[531,626,1636,1662]" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED403824FF74F948FF24F961" box="[177,225,1670,1696]" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FE84F948FE27F95E" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[321,482,1669,1696]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FE84F948FE94F95E" box="[321,337,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FE9BF94BFE27F95E" box="[350,482,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in the setation of the first exopodal and endopodal segments of leg 1, each of which bears an innerseta (cf. absentin 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FE23F904FD40F922" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[486,645,1737,1764]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FE23F904FE33F922" box="[486,502,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FDC4F907FD40F922" box="[513,645,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the caudal rami are distinct (fused to anal somite in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FD92F922FD3CF8C4" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[599,761,1771,1798]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FD92F922FDA2F8C4" box="[599,615,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FDB0F925FD3CF8C4" box="[629,761,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the first endopodal segment of leg 4 is unarmed (cf. bears an inner seta in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FEF8F8FEFE1AF88B" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[317,479,1840,1866]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FEF8F8FEFE88F888" box="[317,333,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FE9EF8FEFE1AF88B" box="[347,479,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and leg 5 is bilobed (leg 5 consists of 1 inner seta and an apparently bipartite outer lobe in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FF19F8BAFEBBF84F" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[220,382,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FF19F8BAFF29F84C" box="[220,236,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FF3FF8BAFEBBF84F" box="[250,382,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED403824FF78F858FE86F7D7" blockId="529.[136,778,1635,2070]" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">
The third exopodal segment of leg 4 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FDAFF858FCCFF871" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[618,778,1942,1968]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FDAFF858FDBFF86E" box="[618,634,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED403824FD43F858FCCFF871" box="[646,778,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="529" pageNumber="530">ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is armed with 9 setae (formula 3, 1, 5), such a setation pattern is extremely unusual for a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED403824FF4DF832FEFAF7D7" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[136,319,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="529" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodelphyidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
